1
00:00:14,742 --> 00:00:20,180
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:21,015 --> 00:00:28,922
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,990 --> 00:00:34,360
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,429 --> 00:00:38,490
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,734 --> 00:00:44,637
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,373 --> 00:00:52,279
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,681 --> 00:00:57,173
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:57,251 --> 00:01:04,157
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:04,292 --> 00:01:11,357
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,432 --> 00:01:18,099
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,506 --> 00:01:28,074
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:49,748 --> 00:01:51,511
<i>Heh! It's over...</i>

13
00:01:54,586 --> 00:01:59,319
<i>Losing is not an Option</i>

14
00:02:00,726 --> 00:02:01,522
<i>What?!</i>

15
00:02:08,967 --> 00:02:09,797
<i>Just barely...</i>

16
00:02:10,235 --> 00:02:11,634
<i>That was a close one.</i>

17
00:02:12,404 --> 00:02:14,964
<i>But...I was able to throw it off</i>
<i>just a little.</i>

18
00:02:16,175 --> 00:02:17,403
<i>There's no mistake.</i>

19
00:02:18,544 --> 00:02:21,479
<i>He's now realized the secret</i>
<i>of the Byakugan.</i>

20
00:02:24,016 --> 00:02:26,610
<i>What's the meaning of this?</i>
<i>How?!</i>

21
00:02:31,724 --> 00:02:33,316
<i>How was he able to throw it</i>

22
00:02:33,392 --> 00:02:35,383
<i>a whole six inches</i>
<i>from his vital point?!</i>

23
00:02:43,302 --> 00:02:45,532
<i>I see... That Chakra!</i>

24
00:02:45,938 --> 00:02:49,101
<i>He was emitting Chakra</i>
<i>the whole time</i>

25
00:02:49,174 --> 00:02:51,233
<i>and covered the area surrounding him!</i>

26
00:02:52,544 --> 00:02:54,876
<i>And in a wide range to that extent.</i>

27
00:02:56,548 --> 00:02:58,743
<i>No wonder he was able</i>
<i>to detect the arrow and</i>

28
00:02:58,817 --> 00:03:01,911
<i>throw off the trajectory of it.</i>

29
00:03:05,824 --> 00:03:10,227
<i>But constantly emitting that</i>
<i>much Chakra is a death throe...</i>

30
00:03:11,830 --> 00:03:14,060
<i>If he doesn't go that far,</i>
<i>he can't dodge.</i>

31
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:16,333
<i>In other words, there's no mistake.</i>

32
00:03:16,869 --> 00:03:18,200
<i>It's as I hypothesized...</i>

33
00:03:19,037 --> 00:03:22,803
<i>The arrow earlier was</i>
<i>totally invisible to him!</i>

34
00:03:24,710 --> 00:03:27,110
<i>He doesn't carry out useless attacks...</i>

35
00:03:27,446 --> 00:03:30,711
<i>And from the results,</i>
<i>he accurately examines the information.</i>

36
00:03:38,357 --> 00:03:41,724
<i>And...he's also discovered</i>
<i>the weakness of my eyes...</i>

37
00:03:41,894 --> 00:03:42,861
<i>Impressive.</i>

38
00:03:46,165 --> 00:03:48,463
<i>Of all the enemies</i>
<i>I've fought until now,</i>

39
00:03:48,734 --> 00:03:50,258
<i>this guy's the strongest!</i>

40
00:03:53,005 --> 00:03:55,303
<i>He has 360 degree sight.</i>

41
00:03:56,508 --> 00:03:59,068
<i>And he unfailingly detects attacks</i>

42
00:03:59,144 --> 00:04:02,773
<i>that penetrate the roughly</i>
<i>150 feeot circumference around him.</i>

43
00:04:04,383 --> 00:04:05,350
<i>But for some reason,</i>

44
00:04:05,417 --> 00:04:08,250
<i>there were Kunai Knives</i>
<i>he couldn't evade completely.</i>

45
00:04:10,189 --> 00:04:12,419
<i>Why couldn't he evade them?</i>

46
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:16,253
<i>Because he couldn't see them!</i>

47
00:04:17,362 --> 00:04:21,731
<i>In other words, even his Visual Jutsu</i>
<i>has a slight blind spot!</i>

48
00:04:22,901 --> 00:04:26,098
<i>Being unable to see Kunai Knives</i>
<i>entering that blind spot,</i>

49
00:04:26,171 --> 00:04:27,433
<i>he's unable to react.</i>

50
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:30,768
<i>So he was dealing with attacks</i>
<i>from the blind spot</i>

51
00:04:30,843 --> 00:04:33,073
<i>with that defense technique.</i>

52
00:04:33,946 --> 00:04:37,780
<i>And I analyzed all the attacks</i>
<i>I carried out</i>

53
00:04:37,850 --> 00:04:39,715
<i>and grasped them perfectly.</i>

54
00:04:40,752 --> 00:04:43,220
<i>Right behind his first thoracic vertebra...</i>

55
00:04:43,288 --> 00:04:46,724
<i>there exists a blind spot expanding</i>
<i>from a very small point.</i>

56
00:04:58,904 --> 00:05:01,702
<i>Indeed, if he moves and</i>
<i>doesn't stabilize the blind spot,</i>

57
00:05:01,773 --> 00:05:04,503
<i>it becomes difficult to aim there</i>
<i>with an arrow.</i>

58
00:05:04,843 --> 00:05:08,108
<i>But such a trick... doesn't fool me!</i>

59
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:13,847
<i>Gentle Fist is pointless if</i>
<i>you don't come close to your enemy.</i>

60
00:05:14,253 --> 00:05:18,883
<i>And you can't afford to think about</i>
<i>approaching me at this point.</i>

61
00:05:19,458 --> 00:05:21,255
<i>It's about how to escape now...</i>

62
00:05:22,194 --> 00:05:26,460
<i>Though whether you struggle or not,</i>
<i>you're going to die anyway.</i>

63
00:05:32,337 --> 00:05:35,363
<i>Heh... It seems you only</i>
<i>have a little Chakra left.</i>

64
00:05:37,643 --> 00:05:39,702
<i>The fate of the small fry character</i>
<i>in an easy game</i>

65
00:05:39,778 --> 00:05:41,678
<i>is to be destroyed right away!</i>

66
00:05:45,717 --> 00:05:46,706
<i>It's useless!</i>

67
00:06:56,555 --> 00:06:57,681
<i>A thread?!</i>

68
00:06:59,191 --> 00:07:01,056
<i>I see, with this thread...</i>

69
00:07:05,831 --> 00:07:08,095
<i>This time, the trajectory was thrown off</i>
<i>slightly by the trees, huh?</i>

70
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:18,133
<i>If that's the case...</i>

71
00:07:18,443 --> 00:07:21,412
<i>I'll add some rotation this time.</i>

72
00:07:22,014 --> 00:07:23,641
<i>So even if it hits a tree,</i>

73
00:07:23,715 --> 00:07:27,378
<i>it'll just cut through and the trajectory</i>
<i>won't be thrown off.</i>

74
00:07:27,619 --> 00:07:29,746
<i>And as before...</i>

75
00:07:29,888 --> 00:07:33,119
<i>I'll control the arrow up until</i>
<i>150 feet away from him</i>

76
00:07:33,191 --> 00:07:34,886
<i>using a thread with Chakra</i>
<i>flowing through.</i>

77
00:07:35,427 --> 00:07:37,554
<i>I'll take aim at the moving target...</i>

78
00:07:37,629 --> 00:07:40,723
<i>and plunge the arrow into</i>
<i>the blind spot with a pinpoint attack!</i>

79
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:46,631
<i>He's still standing up?</i>

80
00:07:47,472 --> 00:07:51,169
<i>He's strong...</i>
<i>He's much stronger than me.</i>

81
00:07:52,844 --> 00:07:54,835
<i>I hardly have any Chakra left now.</i>

82
00:07:55,614 --> 00:07:58,640
<i>I probably won't be able to evade</i>
<i>his next attack completely.</i>

83
00:07:59,651 --> 00:08:00,845
<i>Is this it?</i>

84
00:08:03,321 --> 00:08:05,050
<i>I'll win no matter what!</i>

85
00:08:11,196 --> 00:08:13,892
<i>Naruto... I wonder what you'd do.</i>

86
00:08:16,868 --> 00:08:17,800
I've had enough.

87
00:08:20,072 --> 00:08:22,905
I can't dodge it anyway.

88
00:08:29,314 --> 00:08:32,374
<i>He's stopped moving...</i>
<i>Has he given up?</i>

89
00:08:33,452 --> 00:08:35,750
<i>But just to make doubly sure...</i>

90
00:08:36,455 --> 00:08:40,619
<i>Maximum destructive power</i>
<i>with 120% accuracy.</i>

91
00:09:02,447 --> 00:09:03,345
<i>I've got him!</i>

92
00:09:29,074 --> 00:09:30,200
<i>This is it.</i>

93
00:09:31,676 --> 00:09:32,506
<i>Gentle Fist!</i>

94
00:10:08,046 --> 00:10:11,038
<i>Wh-What? He still...?!</i>

95
00:10:11,483 --> 00:10:15,283
<i>No! My attack just now</i>
<i>should've made the kill.</i>

96
00:10:15,954 --> 00:10:18,320
<i>Substance with Chakra base...</i>

97
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:20,517
<i>It's meaningless against Gentle Fist.</i>

98
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,088
<i>Gentle Fist...</i>

99
00:10:23,161 --> 00:10:25,129
<i>I see, in his final moments,</i>

100
00:10:25,197 --> 00:10:27,631
<i>he funneled the last Chakra</i>
<i>through the thread!</i>

101
00:10:36,942 --> 00:10:37,806
<i>Eight crows...</i>

102
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:42,442
<i>Again I couldn't see one of them.</i>

103
00:10:47,018 --> 00:10:48,110
<i>What happened to him?</i>

104
00:10:56,528 --> 00:10:58,792
<i>He damaged several of</i>
<i>my internal organs.</i>

105
00:10:59,231 --> 00:11:01,563
<i>But...I can still move.</i>

106
00:11:10,609 --> 00:11:11,940
<i>You failure...</i>

107
00:11:13,578 --> 00:11:19,983
<i>I told you... I don't know when to quit!</i>

108
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:25,947
<i>Why do you try to go against</i>
<i>your destiny that much?</i>

109
00:11:26,925 --> 00:11:31,089
<i>Because I was called...a failure!</i>

110
00:11:34,499 --> 00:11:38,060
<i>But if you're going to say it's futile,</i>
<i>you don't have to do anything!</i>

111
00:11:38,303 --> 00:11:43,036
<i>After I become the Hokage,</i>
<i>I'll change Hyuga!</i>

112
00:11:44,776 --> 00:11:46,801
<i>The Ninjutsu that you're good at, huh?</i>

113
00:11:47,712 --> 00:11:48,940
<i>I was careless...</i>

114
00:11:50,515 --> 00:11:55,782
<i>Clone Jutsu was the Ninjutsu</i>
<i>I stunk at.</i>

115
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:02,492
<i>Don't be whining about boring stuff</i>
<i>like destiny and what not,</i>

116
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:05,393
<i>and how it can't be changed!</i>

117
00:12:06,064 --> 00:12:08,532
<i>Unlike me,</i>

118
00:12:08,867 --> 00:12:10,528
<i>you're not a failure.</i>

119
00:12:15,073 --> 00:12:16,199
<i>Naruto...</i>

120
00:12:16,741 --> 00:12:19,403
Now it's become the three of us...

121
00:12:20,178 --> 00:12:22,112
Don't worry about such things.

122
00:12:22,514 --> 00:12:24,744
Both Choji and Neji will
catch up right away.

123
00:12:28,253 --> 00:12:30,084
Choji had the trump card.

124
00:12:30,922 --> 00:12:35,018
And I've fought Neji
in the Chunin exam, so I know...

125
00:12:35,794 --> 00:12:36,658
Know what?

126
00:12:38,463 --> 00:12:42,923
That he's... a true genius. Believe it!

127
00:12:45,737 --> 00:12:47,500
<i>I cannot lose...</i>

128
00:12:48,873 --> 00:12:51,535
<i>Whether he's an enemy</i>
<i>much stronger than me...</i>

129
00:12:51,609 --> 00:12:53,338
<i>or even if this body should fail me...</i>

130
00:12:53,912 --> 00:12:55,641
<i>I cannot lose!</i>

131
00:12:58,283 --> 00:13:01,741
<i>I have a reason why I cannot lose!</i>

132
00:13:14,132 --> 00:13:17,067
<i>I've had a hard time of it this time.</i>

133
00:13:21,239 --> 00:13:22,501
<i>I played too long...</i>

134
00:13:23,575 --> 00:13:24,166
<i>Huh?</i>

135
00:13:52,771 --> 00:13:54,568
<i>I can't build up Chakra...</i>

136
00:13:54,773 --> 00:13:57,207
How? You should've
been instantly killed!

137
00:13:57,842 --> 00:13:59,207
How come you're alive?!

138
00:13:59,778 --> 00:14:01,973
I couldn't completely
evade it anyway.

139
00:14:03,114 --> 00:14:06,242
So I was prepared to deliberately
take the hit.

140
00:14:07,619 --> 00:14:11,419
And I knew of my own weakness
much more than you do...

141
00:14:12,557 --> 00:14:15,390
<i>There were eight crows, huh?</i>

142
00:14:16,761 --> 00:14:18,820
This Byakugan has a blind spot.

143
00:14:19,798 --> 00:14:23,928
However, if I knew that your attack
would only come from there...

144
00:14:24,436 --> 00:14:28,065
I could release my Chakra just
to that blind spot and detect the attack.

145
00:14:28,606 --> 00:14:30,164
It's not so difficult to make

146
00:14:30,241 --> 00:14:33,699
a move of just a few inches
to throw off the aim.

147
00:14:34,345 --> 00:14:37,007
I'd suffer a serious injury,
but instant death can be avoided.

148
00:14:41,586 --> 00:14:43,486
So you took the hit deliberately...?

149
00:14:43,555 --> 00:14:45,853
It doesn't change the fact
that you're going to die here.

150
00:14:47,091 --> 00:14:48,820
How can you go that far?!

151
00:14:50,595 --> 00:14:55,362
"Of all the enemies,"
you're the strongest I've ever fought...

152
00:14:56,601 --> 00:15:00,002
But, there's a reason why I cannot lose.

153
00:15:02,574 --> 00:15:09,343
Of all those I've ever fought,
the strongest one said this to me...

154
00:15:12,784 --> 00:15:16,686
- Unlike me... you are not a failure!
- <i>Unlike me... you are not a failure!</i>

155
00:15:18,323 --> 00:15:19,187
He said that.

156
00:15:21,392 --> 00:15:23,553
I've been called a genius all along.

157
00:15:24,696 --> 00:15:26,823
So I cannot lose.

158
00:15:28,032 --> 00:15:29,897
And for the sake of those guys
who believe

159
00:15:29,968 --> 00:15:32,937
that this humdrum and small me
is a genius!

160
00:15:42,413 --> 00:15:44,973
"The fate of the small fry character
in a game is to be destroyed right away."

161
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:46,849
You said that, didn't you?

162
00:15:57,795 --> 00:15:59,387
Look at this situation!

163
00:16:02,934 --> 00:16:06,768
Things like fate,
isn't determined by someone!

164
00:16:12,310 --> 00:16:13,641
I wonder...

165
00:16:14,212 --> 00:16:16,874
You also look like
you're going to die!

166
00:16:23,321 --> 00:16:25,949
<i>Neji, live.</i>

167
00:16:26,524 --> 00:16:28,617
<i>More than anyone in the clan,</i>

168
00:16:28,693 --> 00:16:31,253
<i>you're the man loved most</i>
<i>by the Hyuga ability...</i>

169
00:16:34,632 --> 00:16:39,092
I cannot die so easily.

170
00:16:41,506 --> 00:16:45,670
Even if you act tough,
you can't stem the current now...

171
00:16:46,511 --> 00:16:50,675
Master Sasuke ran to
the Sound Village by his own wish.

172
00:16:57,221 --> 00:17:00,349
<i>Sasuke is now in the darkness...</i>

173
00:17:08,066 --> 00:17:08,964
No...

174
00:17:11,669 --> 00:17:16,402
<i>Naruto... You've got better eyes than me.</i>

175
00:17:18,343 --> 00:17:23,781
There's a person who can find him
in the darkness and save him.

176
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:28,316
Master Sasuke belongs
to Lord Orochimaru.

177
00:17:31,222 --> 00:17:33,588
No matter who it may be,
they can't save...

178
00:17:33,658 --> 00:17:34,647
He <i>can</i> save him!

179
00:17:42,166 --> 00:17:46,762
<i>Because...Naruto...you...</i>

180
00:17:50,241 --> 00:17:53,233
<i>You saved me from the darkness!</i>

181
00:18:03,488 --> 00:18:05,251
Talking rubbish until the end...

182
00:18:08,660 --> 00:18:09,592
<i>But...</i>

183
00:18:10,695 --> 00:18:14,722
<i>I haven't been pushed this far</i>
<i>since Kimimaro.</i>

184
00:18:22,340 --> 00:18:24,365
<i>Damn it...</i>

185
00:19:37,081 --> 00:19:37,979
<i>Everyone...</i>

186
00:19:43,755 --> 00:19:44,813
<i>I'll leave the rest...</i>

187
00:19:46,157 --> 00:19:47,419
<i>to you.</i>

188
00:21:12,578 --> 00:21:14,978
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

189
00:21:15,047 --> 00:21:18,073
<i>And you smiled</i>

190
00:21:18,317 --> 00:21:20,615
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

191
00:21:20,686 --> 00:21:23,416
<i>In my own words</i>

192
00:21:23,488 --> 00:21:29,051
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

193
00:21:29,394 --> 00:21:34,593
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

194
00:21:34,867 --> 00:21:40,271
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

195
00:21:40,472 --> 00:21:46,001
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

196
00:21:46,979 --> 00:21:52,178
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

197
00:21:52,584 --> 00:21:59,251
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

198
00:21:59,758 --> 00:22:02,454
<i>I feel so sad</i>

199
00:22:02,527 --> 00:22:03,425
<i>But...</i>

200
00:22:03,495 --> 00:22:05,895
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

201
00:22:05,964 --> 00:22:08,933
<i>And you smiled</i>

202
00:22:09,067 --> 00:22:11,661
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

203
00:22:11,737 --> 00:22:14,729
<i>In my own words</i>

204
00:22:14,907 --> 00:22:17,239
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

205
00:22:17,309 --> 00:22:20,437
<i>And you smiled</i>

206
00:22:20,512 --> 00:22:22,980
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

207
00:22:23,048 --> 00:22:25,949
<i>In my own words</i>

208
00:22:26,018 --> 00:22:30,580
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

209
00:22:39,631 --> 00:22:42,293
Yahoo! The enemies are quite close!

210
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:44,631
All right! We'll catch up in a burst!

211
00:22:44,703 --> 00:22:46,295
Speaking in terms of number,
we've got more!

212
00:22:46,371 --> 00:22:47,963
If things go well,
we can get him back next!

213
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:50,804
Yeah! I don't feel like losing
with four against two!

214
00:22:50,943 --> 00:22:51,807
Four against two?

215
00:22:51,877 --> 00:22:52,866
That's twice the opponents' number!

216
00:22:52,945 --> 00:22:54,412
Say say. Were there four of us?

217
00:22:54,479 --> 00:22:58,245
Are you an idiot?!
Me, Akamaru, Shikamaru, and you!

